This paper deals with generating textures and images using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses incorporating long-range structure and symmetry constraints, which are topics related to graphics (cs.GR). The modification proposed in the paper involves altering the representation of features in the CNN, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) topic. Finally, the paper presents applications to inpainting and season transfer, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
